Salary is personal data under GDPR Art. 4(1) when linked to an identifiable employee, but not a special category under Art. 9. CIA classification: Confidentiality = High (sensitive HR/financial data, internal-only, risk of harm and discrimination if disclosed); Integrity = High (drives payroll, tax, and contractual obligations — tampering causes financial and legal damage); Availability = Medium (needed for payroll cycles, but short outages are tolerable). Lawful basis typically Art. 6(1)(b) contract and 6(1)(c) legal obligation. Apply data minimization, role-based access, encryption at rest and in transit, and audit logging. Retention limited to statutory payroll/tax periods (commonly ~6–10 years depending on jurisdiction).
